1
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:10,416
[KIMURA]
Forget the test!

2
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,166
I'm gonna die if I have
to study any longer!

3
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:14,541
I'm hittin' the arcade.

4
00:00:14,625 --> 00:00:16,333
[SAKURAI, TAKAO]
Well, we can't let you go alone!

5
00:00:16,416 --> 00:00:18,500
Hey, Nishikata, are you comin'?

6
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:19,916
I don't know about you,

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,708
but when I study for too long,
it just doesn't stick.

8
00:00:21,791 --> 00:00:22,583
Uhh.

9
00:00:22,666 --> 00:00:24,083
Sorry, I think I'm gonna stay.

10
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:26,541
You've made your choice!

11
00:00:26,625 --> 00:00:28,083
Later!

12
00:00:29,083 --> 00:00:30,458
[KIMURA]
What are you guys gonna play?

13
00:00:30,541 --> 00:00:32,666
[SAKURAI] Whichever gets me
one of those cute figures.

14
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:33,625
[NISHIKATA]
Man.

15
00:00:33,708 --> 00:00:34,625
I'm jealous.

16
00:00:34,708 --> 00:00:36,708
But I can't think about them.

17
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:39,041
I have to get a
good grade on my next test!

18
00:00:39,125 --> 00:00:40,125
Or else!

19
00:00:40,208 --> 00:00:41,708
Hey.

20
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,958
Can I sit here?

21
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,083
Studying for the test?

22
00:00:49,166 --> 00:00:50,541
Yeah. I am.

23
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:24,125
[NISHIKATA]
"Studying for the Test."

24
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:28,833
[TAKAGI] I just saw your
friends leaving as I came in.

25
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:30,041
Yeah.

26
00:02:30,125 --> 00:02:32,458
We were all studying
together for a while.

27
00:02:33,458 --> 00:02:34,916
[TAKAGI]
Ahh...

28
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,291
Well I heard them talking,

29
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:38,750
and I figured they were
on their way to the arcade.

30
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,916
Are you not going with them?

31
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,583
I don't have time to
play around like they do.

32
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:48,458
If I don't score within the top
fifty of my grade on this test.

33
00:02:48,541 --> 00:02:51,250
My parents are taking
away my video games.

34
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,208
[TAKAGI]
Huuuh.

35
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:54,958
I see.

36
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:58,166
[NISHIKATA]
Oh, no!

37
00:02:58,250 --> 00:02:59,875
Why am I telling her everything?

38
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:01,166
Now that she knows,

39
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:02,958
she's totally gonna
distract me from studying!

40
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,458
Nice going, me.

41
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:11,958
I.. was just kidding?

42
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:13,625
About what?

43
00:03:13,708 --> 00:03:16,333
Ugh. Forget it.

44
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:18,750
Anyway, don't interrupt
me this time.

45
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,083
[TAKAGI]
That's mean.

46
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:22,250
You say that like I'm always
getting in your way.

47
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,375
[NISHIKATA]
That's because you are!

48
00:03:24,458 --> 00:03:29,500
Well, yeah. It's 'cuz it's so
fun to tease you, Nishikata!

49
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:30,458
[NISHIKATA growls]

50
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:32,416
Should I study somewhere else?

51
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:36,125
No, if I did that, I'd basically
be letting her win.

52
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,041
I just realized.

53
00:03:40,125 --> 00:03:41,583
You're not studying?

54
00:03:41,666 --> 00:03:43,041
Nope.

55
00:03:43,125 --> 00:03:45,708
I like to limit myself to
two hours of studying a day.

56
00:03:45,791 --> 00:03:46,875
Oh.

57
00:03:48,041 --> 00:03:49,833
[NISHIKATA]
I shouldn't be surprised.

58
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:53,541
She easily scores in the top
ten of our grade all the time.

59
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:57,375
But, what does
she have up her sleeve?

60
00:03:57,458 --> 00:03:59,208
This is Takagi
we're talking about.

61
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:01,833
She's definitely gonna
try to mess with me.

62
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:03,333
I mean, how could she not?

63
00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:05,750
It's practically in her blood!

64
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:06,708
[TAKAGI]
Hmm? What's up?

65
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:09,250
Huh? Oh, nothing, just thinking.

66
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,208
It's not like
I was looking at you.

67
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:12,250
I just kinda
spaced out--

68
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:15,291
By the way,
you got that one wrong.

69
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:16,750
Problem six, where it says,

70
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:21,166
"Solve for x over negative
two plus three y." That one.

71
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:22,750
[NISHIKATA]
You mean it's not 15?

72
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:23,875
[TAKAGI]
Mm-hmm.

73
00:04:23,958 --> 00:04:25,083
[NISHIKATA]
What? Really?

74
00:04:25,166 --> 00:04:27,041
[TAKAGI]
Mm-hmm.

75
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:29,416
Substitute the numbers.

76
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:30,583
Was that wrong?

77
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,791
No. So then...

78
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:38,333
Here we go.

79
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:41,083
[NISHIKATA]
Uh... What are you...?

80
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:46,791
It's easier to
teach you this way.

81
00:04:46,875 --> 00:04:49,125
So, x equals negative 16...

82
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:50,291
[NISHIKATA]
"Easier to."

83
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:52,375
She's teaching me?

84
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:54,500
What is she planning?

85
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:56,458
Write it out. Go ahead.

86
00:04:57,916 --> 00:04:59,291
There's a negative
times a negative

87
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:01,375
and don't forget
order of operations.

88
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:03,000
It's "PEMDAS" remember?

89
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:04,125
[NISHIKATA]
Oh yeah!

90
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:05,250
Then let's see.

91
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:07,583
It's five!

92
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:09,208
Yep. That's right!

93
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:11,000
Oh! And for these next ones,
you should be able...

94
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:12,375
[NISHIKATA]
She's amazing.

95
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:15,000
She can figure it out
with just a glance.

96
00:05:15,083 --> 00:05:16,791
Hey. I appreciate this.

97
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:19,416
I was really struggling
with this page before.

98
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:22,291
Why don't I teach
you from the beginning?

99
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:25,958
[NISHIKATA] She's gonna
teach me the whole thing?

100
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:28,333
I'm saved!

101
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:30,625
No, something's fishy here!

102
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:31,875
Why is she being so nice?

103
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:35,083
She's never this nice
unless she's teasing me!

104
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:36,875
[NISHIKATA]
Hey, Takagi.

105
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:39,791
Why are you being
so nice to me today?

106
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:40,541
[TAKAGI]
Hmm?

107
00:05:40,625 --> 00:05:42,125
What do you mean?

108
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:45,750
Well, you're just being
kinder than usual.

109
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:46,958
So...

110
00:05:47,041 --> 00:05:49,375
Oh... Right.

111
00:05:49,458 --> 00:05:52,708
I am always teasing you
in the middle of class.

112
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:57,083
I would feel really bad if your
grades went down because of me.

113
00:05:58,083 --> 00:06:00,625
Nishikata.

114
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:03,166
I'm sorry for teasing
you every single day.

115
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:05,833
Let me help you get
a better grade.

116
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:08,500
Takagi.

117
00:06:09,541 --> 00:06:11,000
[NISHIKATA]
I don't believe it.

118
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:14,208
You've finally seen
the error in your ways!

119
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:17,125
All right, let's go for it!

120
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,541
[TAKAGI]
Thanks for the juice.

121
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:22,125
[NISHIKATA]
No, thank you.

122
00:06:22,208 --> 00:06:25,541
I made huge progress on my math
today, because I had your help.

123
00:06:26,166 --> 00:06:27,125
[NISHIKATA]
And now I'm less likely

124
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:29,250
to have my games taken away.

125
00:06:31,041 --> 00:06:32,041
[NISHIKATA]
Maybe Takagi is actually

126
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,041
a good person, after all.

127
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:36,166
Really.

128
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:37,708
Thank you so much for today.

129
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:38,708
Oh, no.

130
00:06:38,791 --> 00:06:41,041
You shouldn't thank me.

131
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:46,083
Since what I taught you,
won't be on the test.

132
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,791
Wha... Hey! Hold on!

133
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:54,875
[TAKAGI] You're good
at substitution now, right?

134
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:56,375
[NISHIKATA] Yeah,
and a lot of good that'll do!

135
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:58,166
Gimme back that juice right now!

136
00:06:58,250 --> 00:06:59,375
[TAKAGI]
Oops, I already opened it.

137
00:06:59,458 --> 00:07:01,083
[NISHIKATA]
You literally just opened it!

138
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:03,708
[YUKARI]
"Test."

139
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:06,791
Pass your answer sheets forward.

140
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:11,041
[YUKARI]
I think I did pretty well.

141
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,541
I should've
gotten a 90 at least.

142
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:16,166
[MINA]
Hey, Yukari?

143
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:18,125
[SANAE]
Can you teach me this?

144
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:20,458
I just can't seem
to do well in English.

145
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:24,625
Huh? You make it sound like
you're good at everything else.

146
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:26,708
No, I'm just
extra bad at English!

147
00:07:26,791 --> 00:07:27,625
Anyway!

148
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:28,583
Help me out here!

149
00:07:28,666 --> 00:07:30,041
In this part--

150
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:32,791
Sorry, no can do.

151
00:07:32,875 --> 00:07:34,833
I want to review
before the next test, too.

152
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:37,916
Huh?! But you always
help me study between tests!

153
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,416
[YUKARI]
This time is different.

154
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,333
If I can get a 90
or above on everything,

155
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:44,166
my parents are buying
me any game I want.

156
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:48,208
Cool. So this part's
been really tripping me up.

157
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:49,875
Were you listening?

158
00:07:49,958 --> 00:07:51,041
I don't have the time

159
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:52,666
to teach you guys
this stuff last minute.

160
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:53,250
[MINA]
Meanie!

161
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:54,500
Buzz off. Shoo.

162
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:55,541
What's more important?

163
00:07:55,625 --> 00:07:57,541
Our friendship
or some stupid game?

164
00:07:57,625 --> 00:07:58,708
Yeah, what she said.

165
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:00,291
Sure you can play video games,

166
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:02,500
but you can't teach them like
you can your best friends!

167
00:08:02,583 --> 00:08:04,083
Yeah, what she said.

168
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:06,208
[sighs]

169
00:08:06,291 --> 00:08:07,875
[YUKARI] Now that those
two academic train wrecks

170
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:11,291
will leave me alone,
I should review.

171
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:13,791
All right, I'm handing
out the next test.

172
00:08:13,875 --> 00:08:15,583
Take one and pass it back.

173
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:17,750
[YUKARI] Okay, I've thoroughly
reviewed the material

174
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:19,291
right before the test.

175
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:21,166
Now that I've got
English fresh in the brain,

176
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,541
this'll be a--

177
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:25,041
Math?

178
00:08:27,458 --> 00:08:29,208
[NISHIKATA]
"Test Results."

179
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:31,583
[TEACHER]
Here.

180
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:34,458
Did you study at all this time?

181
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:35,291
Next.

182
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:36,833
Saitou.

183
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:38,958
You're looking
nervous over there.

184
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:39,875
No, I'm not.

185
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:41,208
[TEACHER]
Takagi.

186
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:42,958
Yes!

187
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:47,875
You did very well, as usual.

188
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:50,291
[MINA]
She's so smart.

189
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:53,125
[FEMALE STUDENT]
Sounds like you did fine Takagi.

190
00:08:53,208 --> 00:08:54,708
Can we compare answers later?

191
00:08:54,791 --> 00:08:55,833
[TAKAGI]
Sure.

192
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:56,541
So.

193
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:58,958
You get a good grade?

194
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:00,791
Yeah, but not a hundred percent.

195
00:09:00,875 --> 00:09:02,458
[NISHIKATA]
That sounds about right.

196
00:09:02,541 --> 00:09:04,958
But I got this
one in the bag, too.

197
00:09:05,041 --> 00:09:05,958
[TEACHER]
Next up, Nishikata!

198
00:09:06,041 --> 00:09:07,458
Right!

199
00:09:09,041 --> 00:09:11,458
[TEACHER] You can do
a little better next time.

200
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,708
Was it that bad?

201
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,333
[NISHIKATA]
As if you care at all!

202
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:20,541
You're the one who taught me
stuff that wasn't on the test!

203
00:09:20,625 --> 00:09:22,583
All up on your high horse
because you got a good score!

204
00:09:22,666 --> 00:09:23,458
Whatever!

205
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:26,291
[TAKAGI]
Hey. Hey!

206
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:27,541
Guess my score.

207
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,250
And I'll guess yours.

208
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,291
Whoever gets closer will win.

209
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:34,083
You're always proposing
this stuff out of nowhere.

210
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:35,791
But okay.

211
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:38,875
Uh... Is it around 50?

212
00:09:38,958 --> 00:09:40,000
[NISHIKATA]
Hmph!

213
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:42,041
You underestimate me
too much, Takagi.

214
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:43,708
You think so?

215
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:47,666
Okay, then did you
get above 60 percent?

216
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:51,125
[TAKAGI]
I'll take that as a no.

217
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,708
[NISHIKATA]
How did she know?

218
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:54,250
Give her your poker face.

219
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:57,333
Confuse her with your world
class, unwavering poker face!

220
00:09:57,416 --> 00:09:59,833
Did you get above 55?

221
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:03,625
[TAKAGI]
That's a yes.

222
00:10:03,708 --> 00:10:05,166
[NISHIKATA]
Why?

223
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:08,583
That leaves everything
between 55 and 59.

224
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:11,833
[NISHIKATA] I have to keep her
from guessing the exact score!

225
00:10:11,916 --> 00:10:14,416
[TAKAGI]
Okay, then.

226
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,083
Fifty-six?

227
00:10:16,166 --> 00:10:17,625
Or...

228
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:20,125
Fifty-seven?

229
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:22,541
Fifty-eight?

230
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:25,125
Fifty-nine?

231
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:26,750
Yup.

232
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,833
I got it.

233
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:30,750
You got a 56.

234
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:33,500
Uhh. Is that the
answer you're going with?

235
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:36,166
[TAKAGI]
Mm-hmm.

236
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:38,208
[NISHIKATA]
Ready to know the truth?

237
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,708
I got a 59!

238
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:42,916
Sucks to be you!

239
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,041
I guess you were
sorta close, though.

240
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:46,875
[TEACHER]
Hey, quiet down.

241
00:10:46,958 --> 00:10:49,000
The only thing that
sucks is your grade.

242
00:10:49,083 --> 00:10:50,666
You're right; I'm sorry.

243
00:10:54,125 --> 00:10:55,291
Fifty-nine, huh?

244
00:10:55,375 --> 00:10:58,208
Looks like I was off by three.

245
00:10:59,041 --> 00:11:00,291
All right.

246
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:02,541
Now it's your turn to try
and guess my score okay?

247
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:04,166
If it's within two percent.

248
00:11:04,250 --> 00:11:05,833
Then you're the winner.

249
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:07,083
[NISHIKATA]
Bring it on!

250
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,500
I'm gonna figure it out
based on her reactions.

251
00:11:09,583 --> 00:11:11,166
The teacher praised
her a second ago,

252
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:14,875
so I bet that means
she got above a 90.

253
00:11:14,958 --> 00:11:17,458
Is it... like, a 92?

254
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:18,833
Uh...

255
00:11:18,916 --> 00:11:19,833
Huh?

256
00:11:19,916 --> 00:11:22,666
What kinda reaction was that?

257
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:26,416
How about a 95?

258
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,083
